    "line": 247,
    "severity": "critical",
    "description": "GetInputVariable checks 'if config != nil' instead of 'if config == nil' when validating that the variable exists. This inverts the error condition: it reports 'undeclared input variable' error when the variable IS declared, and silently continues when it's NOT declared. This causes incorrect variable resolution and misleading error messages.",
    "fix_patch": "--- a/internal/terraform/evaluate.go
+++ b/internal/terraform/evaluate.go
@@ -244,7 +244,7 @@ func (d *evaluationStateData) GetInputVariable(addr addrs.InputVariable, rng tfd
