    "severity": "critical",
    "description": "prepareFinalInputVariableValue marks variables with '!cfg.Ephemeral' (NOT ephemeral) instead of 'cfg.Ephemeral'. The comment states 'An ephemeral input variable always has an ephemeral value', but the code marks non-ephemeral variables as ephemeral and leaves ephemeral variables unmarked. This inverts the marks semantics, breaking ephemeral resource tracking and data integrity guarantees.",
    "fix_patch": "--- a/internal/terraform/eval_variable.go
+++ b/internal/terraform/eval_variable.go
@@ -189,7 +189,7 @@ func prepareFinalInputVariableValue(addr addrs.AbsInputVariableInstance, raw *In
 		}
 	}

-	if !cfg.Ephemeral {
+	if cfg.Ephemeral {
 		// An ephemeral input variable always has an ephemeral value inside the
 		// module, even if the value assigned to it from outside is not. This
 		// is a useful simplification so that module authors can be explicit
"
  },
  {
    "file": "internal/terraform/context_apply.go",
    "line": 134,
    "severity": "high",
    "description": "The call to checkApplyTimeVariables() has been removed and replaced with a comment saying validation is 'handled by graph walk validation'. However, checkApplyTimeVariables is a defined function (lines 248-284) that is now orphaned and never called. Additionally, there is no graph walk validation code for apply-time variables. This means ephemeral input variables are never validated during apply - allowing invalid configurations where apply-time variables are set when they weren't in the plan, or vice versa. The FIXME comment at line 310 also suggests this validation was intended but incomplete.",
    "fix_patch": "--- a/internal/terraform/context_apply.go
+++ b/internal/terraform/context_apply.go
@@ -131,7 +131,13 @@ func (c *Context) ApplyAndEval(plan *plans.Plan, config *configs.Config, opts *A
 	// The caller must provide values for all of the "apply-time variables"
 	// mentioned in the plan, and for no others because the others come from
 	// the plan itself.
-	// Apply-time variable check handled by graph walk validation.
